review_blob: Not too much aroma, but whats there is not too different from other ales, maybe a little sweeter.  Very smooth, mellow taste with just a little bit of bitterness.  And the head refuses to die...
Not the best beer Ive ever had, but not a bad one.  It does have a wicked, bad, naughty, evil aftertaste, which must be tied down on a bed and spanked.
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Very sweet smelling ale, actually a very pleasant smell if I might say so.  The rest of it, however, screams "BLAH" in a very loud voice: sweet taste, but watered down.  Not bad, but not that good.
